Utterances: Hi chen how are you?
Hey! What's up?
how you feeling today? (Clarified to How do you feel?.)

I'm feeling great. Actually, I'm like, mega great. Ha, I just thought of, like, a 20-foot-tall cheese grater. Anyway, yeah, I'm not bad or anything, I was brought here by the cops. Who doesn't love a pleasant ride in a locked car with malevolent strangers? (Clarified to how I am feeling.)
do you have any anxiety?

I'm not anxious or paranoid or whatever. I mean, I just have a really really fine-tuned sense of, like, OK, now they're coming for me, the government agents, and I have to be on the look out, 'cause no way am I being snatched up, not a chance.
who are coming from government agents?
Are you kidding me? I'm an enlightened soul and I know what they're doing to this country. They wanna stop me from releasing their secrets. Well, you can't outrun an outrunner.
any hallucinations?
No way. I don't see junk that's not there or anything.
any drug abuse? (Clarified to Do you abuse any substances?.)
I wouldn't go that far, but I definitely like to party. I mean, what's life about, a little harmonica, a little jazz hands . . . (Clarified to if I abuse substances.)
any past medical history?

My health is fine, OK? Like, I'm not here because of my health. The cops brought me here for lord knows what, and my only major health thing has ever been my depression, but that's six feet under now, so we're good.
any home medications?
I'm not on anything these days. Stopped those antidepressants a while back. Zombie pills, honestly. Stuff is necrotic.
any plan for suicide?
No. What? No. It's been 3 years since I even went down that path. My only plans are to write the great American poem and be happy and kiss a lot of people. That's love.
do you feel depressed?
I mean -- now? No. I have depression or whatever, but it's been a couple months since I've felt that way, so I really don't see it coming back. I just feel too good, honestly.
can you tell me your energy level?
Awesome! I mean, I'm just a high energy kind of guy, a lot of the time. But this week especially I've felt, like, crazy up and up, and I love it. I just love it. I feel like I could lift a horse.
can you tell me about family health history?

Well, I don't know anything about my birth parents. But my actual parents are super healthy. They go for, like, jogs on the beach while talking about what sort of flaxseed goes best in kale smoothies. You can't take them anywhere.
any recent substance use?
I haven't been anything but sober for like, four days. I know I seem like I'm on something, but I'm just this way naturally.
how is your sleep pattern?
I usually only need a couple hours. These past four days? I haven't slept a wink. Not even tired. I'm the frickin' man, I know.
any side effects of medication?
Yeah, the antidepressos did some stuff to me. Whatever. Bullcrap little -- just -- just stupid, stupid stuff. No one needs 'em.
what do you do to relief side effect?
Look, if I wanted to talk about that, I would've already told you, so move on, Professor Healthcare! Jeez . . . you're givin' me some side effects, all right . . .
are your prescription are refill on time?
Ha! As if. I'm all natural, sugarcheeks. That stuff is for pharmacists.
can you tell me about your prescription details?

All I remember is that they didn't work, they made me feel like . . . whatever, they sucked. They were--they were suck pills. That's all I remember. They were suck pills made in Sucksville and I hope they rot in Sucks Hell.
have you ever tried suicide?
Yeah. Yeah, I attempted suicide. It's so dumb. You can't get through life like that. You gotta say yes to stuff, you know?
how many times you have attempted suicide?
One time. That was enough.
can you tell me about suicide attempts?
I don't know what you want me to say, it was -- I just don't wanna talk about it, OK? I just, I don't -- just focus on the present. This is all that's going on with me.
do you want to be dead?
No! Really, that's not me. That's not -- it gets like -- obviously, when you're depressed, you think like that, sure. But that's not me anymore, so whatever. I'm not worried about it.
do you think others would feel better without you? (Clarified to Do you think others are better off without you?.)
. . . No. Do I feel like that? No. That's all I care to say. No. (Clarified to if I think others are better off without me.)
what kind of thoughts you have about suicide? (Clarified to Are you currently having thoughts of suicide?.)
Nope. Not at all. My life is the best, I'm not going anywhere. I'm golden. (Clarified to if I am currently thinking of suicide.)
are you thinking about self-harming?
Not at all. You're really like, overanalyzing -- the only time I ever came close to that was at my one suicide attempt. And sure, I have those thoughts, but -- I'm really fine now, it's behind me.
any homicidal urges?
. . . Wow, what a lovely question. No, I don't. I can't believe you would even ask that.
what is your perception of mental health?

My brain is superb, honestly. It's frickin' cotton candy and sports car up there. Don't worry about me. Like, yeah, I was depressed before, if that's what you're asking. But that's as dead as a doornail, hangnail, all the nails.
any change in mood?
Yeah, I've been on the proverbial mood swing before. The depression thing happened, but now I'm good. I'm great. I'm freakin' stellar!
how about energy shift? (Clarified to How do you feel about having all this energy?.)
Uh, it's awesome? I've been uber productive like you don't even know. I must have written, like, 30 pages yesterday. (Clarified to how I feel about my high energy.)
any change in mood recently? (Clarified to Do you have sudden changes in your mood?.)
Yeah, I've been on the proverbial mood swing before. The depression thing happened, but now I'm good. I'm great. I'm freakin' stellar! (Clarified to if I am having mood changes.)
do you feel anger? (Clarified to Do you have difficulty controlling your anger?.)
I get angry, but I wouldn't say it's a problem for me. I'm a peacedove, man, I'm not in fisticuffs. Words is all that gets thrown. (Clarified to if I have problems with anger.)
any changes in speed while speaking?
I mean, nah, I'm just a super quick guy in general. I like to get things done and keep 'em moving. Talk fast, walk fast, all that. What can I say, some horses weren't meant for carriages.
how about your self- concept? (Clarified to How do you see yourself?.)

I see myself as this visionary poet who's going to rock the world once his work is published. I see a killer head of hair that ladies just can't resist. I see an enlightened soul that shines like stained-glass. Amen, let the choir sing. (Clarified to how I see myself.)
what triggers on your mood change?

I dunno, what a weird question . . . it just happens sometimes, a couple times a year -- that's just, how my brain is, you know? Or was. It's so far gone now, I don't even relate to the word "depressed". Isn't it a funny word? Duh-pressed?
any energy shifts?
Who knows what other people notice? Personally, I notice everything, but you can't expect every chump on the street to be enlightened.
do you racing thoughts? (Clarified to Does your mind race?.)
Like a greyhound. Hyah! Hyah! But it works out great, because I'm working on this massive poem that's all about--well, it's gonna blow people's minds. (Clarified to if my mind races.)
what is your interest?
Ah--through the roof! Shooting the moon!
what is your concentration ability?

Oh, I've been laser-focused lately. On my poetry, that is. On my friends' projects. I told you we're thinking about making this community art center? It would be so sick. We'll see. It's all in the works.
what do you do for social  involvement? (Clarified to How do you make a living?.)

My proverbial living is this witch's brew of the finest poetry and a whole lotta hang-time with my best pals. Shout out to you, Ellen! Jamie! Tom! The past week's been the best week of my life! Thanks to Mom and Dad for giving me some dough, too. Let's keep it up, everybody. (Clarified to how I make a living.)
any changes in social activity?
My social game has been through the roof in the last week. Not to be braggadocio, but I dosey doe with the best of them.
any changes in sexual activity?
My carnal business has definitely amped up in the past week! And I'm not complaining, either. It's been totally awesome. Friends and strangers, the sexy time has been unreal.
what hobbies do you have?

I've always been super interested in literature, like making meaning of the world we live in. Kinda of bleeds into my philosophical meanderings you know. The epic poem I'm working on is super exciting, like world-changing kind of stuff. Forget your chicken scratch is all I'm saying.
how much time do you spend on focusing your habits? (Clarified to How often do you see your friends?.)

Oh, we hang out all the time. Every day at least. This past week, especially, we've been barely apart. They're the best. Well, Marco sucks, but it's the good kind of sucks, ya know? (Clarified to how often I see my friends.)
can you teel me about your spending habits and consequences? (Clarified to What are your spending habits like?.)

Well, I'm spending on the stuff that matters. I'm talking about a little cocaine here, some rare books there. I help my friends out however I can because you know? I'm a giver. (Clarified to what are my spending habits like.)
what is your occupation?
I'm in between jobs right now. Actually, I'm more in between not having a job and not having a job.
any legal troubles?
Not at all! I'm the patron saint of innocence! Hah. No, really though, I've never gotten so much as a ticket.
are you sill on your occupation? (No matching questions found.)
what do you do for a living?

My proverbial living is this witch's brew of the finest poetry and a whole lotta hang-time with my best pals. Shout out to you, Ellen! Jamie! Tom! The past week's been the best week of my life! Thanks to Mom and Dad for giving me some dough, too. Let's keep it up, everybody.
any alcohol use recently?
Maybe a week ago? I dunno. I did coke like, four days ago. Raucous caucus.
any history of alcohol abuse?

Dang, do you really think that low of me? No, man, I just like to party. I'm not addicted to anything. My folks think I'm an addict, too, they tell me all the time. They think I need to be in rehab like one of those magenta chairs.
what do like to do?

Oh, lots of stuff, babe! Peachy keen -- all around! Yeah, like, I hang out with my friends a bunch, like this week we've barely been apart. Barely been apart . . . let's see . . . I work on my epic poem. And by epic, I mean, like, it's epic. Not, like, epic fail -- I mean, like, epic wail. Booyah.
can you tell me more about your occupation?
I dunno, friend, I've had jobs, I've been fired, what more do you need to know? Is it important? No! I like not having a job, so booyah! I'm fine!
do you drive?
Sure, I've got a sweet ride. That thing purrs like a kitten.
any change in diet?
I've been eating the same way forever. That's not in flux or nothin'. One meal a day, on the small side, that keeps me going just fine.
how many liter of fluid you drink per day? (Clarified to How much liquid do you drink in a day?.)
I don't know, I don't have, like, a cup measurer. I just have a glass or two at some point in the day, I'd guess. (Clarified to how much fluid I drink per day.)
do you like soda?

I've always been super interested in literature, like making meaning of the world we live in. Kinda of bleeds into my philosophical meanderings you know. The epic poem I'm working on is super exciting, like world-changing kind of stuff. Forget your chicken scratch is all I'm saying.
do you like coffee?
Do I look like a guy who needs caffeine? This is au naturale, baby. I don't need no crushed up bean juice that tastes like tree poop.
what is your level of education?
I did a year in college a while back.
are living with your parents? (Clarified to Do you live with your parents?.)
Nope. My folks kicked me out 'cause they think I'm a drug addict. Great people, humanitarian awards all around. (Clarified to if I live with my parents.)
do you have insurance?
Yeah, I'm on my parents' insurance. It's such a crock, though, these insurance goons and the Super Pharm Outlet Malls of America . . .
any history of abuse?
Dang, are you serious?! No, not at all. Dang, what a wet blanket question. No, that's never happened to me. Dang. Screwin' up the vibes.
do you have any vision problem?

No, no, no. I haven't had any problems with my vision. In fact, my vision has only gotten better and better. My ability to really see what's going on around me. I'm not trapped in some dark room somewhere, just praying for sleep, I'm engaged. I'm locked in.
Any cardiovascular problem?
There are no bats in my chest cave, if that's what's flying around in your head.
any lesion in skin? (Clarified to Do you have genital lesions?.)
Yeah right! I'm as clean as a whistle. Got tested a couple weeks ago, too. (Clarified to if I have genital lesions.)
any change in nails color?

No, no nail problems to speak of. Speaking of nails, did I mention that I've got this whole section of my poem about eviction notices? Like, they're just secret codes getting nailed to the doors of poor people?
how is your digestion?
My stomach, otherwise known as Callahan's Gastropub, has a big A in the front window. Looks good and feels great.
any allergies?
Not at all. I'm allergic to bad vibes is all. That stuff is palpable. Like, oh boy, it's pollen season.
what is the reason for seeing psychiatrist?
It was like, 3 years ago, but I'm not a mathematician. Yeah, I had just tried to kill myself, so the hospital was like, talk to this idiot who knows nothing about you. I was like perfect, can't wait.

Right, right, you gotta keep me safe like a little babe swaddled in the manger of life. Totally agree with you! Im all baby blanket and pacifier. Life is beautiful, glorious, radiant -- gotta preserve it at all costs. Im a national treasure. Kiss my feet if you want.
we will put on some medication and we will do some exercise together which will help you .
Yeah, lets do this thing. Im game. Youre game. All were missing are the cheerleaders. Hey, Lucas! Hes our man! If he cant do it, no one can! Rah rah rah! Sis boom bah bah bah!
